Good stuff! When you want to level up, create a file `userContent.css` in a folder called `chrome` in your profile (that Firefox hides from you) with this:
```
@font-face {
	font-family: JuliaMono-Regular;
	src:
		local('JuliaMono-Regular'),
		url("<https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/cormullion/juliamono/webfonts/JuliaMono-Regular.woff2>");
}

code {
	font-family: JuliaMono-Light !important;
}```
and all your code will be in the same font... :slightly_smiling_face: Although nothing in the world of fonts is 100% predictable. :shrugging:

